@spec mm_hole_iter_spec  src=tests/specs/mm_hole_iter_spec.lua  loc=98  sha=285f562  cases=3
@exercises midiManager (h.mm)
@surface   mm:notes, mm:modify, mm:delete, mm:ccs, mm:ccsRaw, mm:events
@harness   bareMM

# Intent
  Phase B pin - design/archive/deferred-reindex.md item 2. mm's four iterators skip
  the holes a delete leaves in the sparse note/cc arrays and keep yielding
  survivors past the hole, up to the noteCount/ccCount high-water mark.
  
  The holes only exist mid-modify today (mm:modify compacts at unwind), so
  the spec observes them from inside the modify closure - the exact state
  the deferred-reindex flip (Phase D) makes the whole pipeline run against.

# Helpers
  @fn ppqsOf(iter)  @ 11-16

# Cases
  @case 'notes() skips a mid-array delete hole and yields the survivor past it'  [harness]  @ 20-39
  @case 'ccs() and ccsRaw() skip a mid-array delete hole'  [harness]  @ 43-64
  @case 'events() skips holes in both the note and the cc array'  [harness]  @ 68-96

# Uses (outbound edges)
  @use call mm:notes  @ 28,33,83
  @use call mm:modify  @ 31,54,87
  @use call mm:delete  @ 32,55,88,89
  @use call mm:ccs  @ 51,56,84
  @use call mm:ccsRaw  @ 57
  @use call mm:events  @ 90
